article.headline: Kennesaw St downs Warren Wilson 92-48
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. -- Orlando Coleman scored a game-high 26 points and grabbed 10 rebounds Monday to lead Kennesaw State in a 92-48 victory over Division II school Warren Wilson. Coleman was 12 of 15 from the field as Kennesaw State hosted its first ever regular season tournament. KSU fell to three previous teams in the tournament -Youngstown State, Eastern Kentucky and Florida International- but grabbed their first win in the final matchup. Nigel Pruitt (20 points) and Tanner Wozniak (11 points) both scored in double digits for the KSU Owls (1-3), who finished with a 48.6 percent field goal percentage. Rashad Ali and Justin Gonyea led Warren Wilson with 12 points each but the Warren Wilson Owls (2-3) struggled offensively, only making 18 of 55 (32.7 percent) from the field.
